        <h2>Gateway-Of-India</h2>

        <p>A historical monument and the most iconic landmark of Mumbai.</p>

        <p>Built in 1924, the Gateway of India overlooks the Arabian Sea and is a symbol of India's freedom.</p>

        <!-- Add image for Amber Fort -->

        <img src="https://pohcdn.com/guide/sites/default/files/styles/paragraph__hero_banner__hb_image__1880bp/public/hero_banner/Gateway-to-India_0.jpg" alt="Gateway-Of-India-India_0">
       
        <p>
The Gateway of India symbolizes the intersection of colonial history and national identity. Initially built to honor British imperial power, it blended diverse architectural styles to assert colonial authority. After India’s independence, the Gateway transformed into a symbol of freedom and national pride, marking the end of British rule. Today, it serves as a monument of collective memory, reflecting India’s journey from colonial subjugation to independence and acting as a space for cultural and historical reflection.</p>
       
