        <h2>Ajanta and Ellora Caves</h2>

        <p>Ancient rock-cut cave complexes with stunning murals and sculptures.</p>

        <p>The Ajanta and Ellora Caves in Maharashtra are famous for their Buddhist, Hindu, and Jain temples and their intricate paintings and carvings.</p>

        <img src="https://aurangabadtourism.in/images/places-to-visit/header/ellora-caves-aurangabad-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg" alt="Ajanta and Ellora Caves">
          
        <p>The Ajanta and Ellora Caves are significant for their religious, artistic, and architectural value. Ajanta focuses on Buddhist art and teachings, while Ellora showcases a blend of Buddhism, Hinduism, and Jainism, reflecting religious tolerance. These caves are both spiritual spaces and artistic masterpieces, demonstrating advanced architecture and cultural expression. They stand as symbols of India’s rich religious diversity and artistic heritage.</p>
       
        <h3>REVIEWS</h3>
       
        <p> Shashank :</p>
        <p>The Ajanta and Ellora caves are incredible! The intricate carvings and paintings are stunning. It’s amazing to think about how they were made so long ago. A must-see for anyone interested in history and art.</p>
       
        <p>Priya :</p>
        <p>Visiting these caves was a deeply spiritual experience. The calmness and beauty of the surroundings, combined with the fascinating stories told through the artwork, make it a place of reflection and awe.</p>
